The paper presents a new model for natural images that can be learned on large-scale datasets and provides a strong image prior for image restoration tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep convolutional networks and high-dimensional latent spaces, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a special manifold structure, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
